BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 10 (KCNA) -- The Korea-Cuba 
Solidarity Committee met in Pyongyang on June 9. 
  Present at the meeting were Choe Ki-yong, chairman of the 
State Education Commission, who is the chairman of the 
Korea-Cuba Solidarity Committee, and officials concerned. 
  Cuban Ambassador to Korea Jose Ramon Rodriguez Varona and 
his 
embassy officials were present on invitation. 
  The meeting discussed questions of commemorating the 
centenary of the death of Jose Marti, the national hero of the 
Cuban people. 

